Chainlink VRF Contract Addresses
Suggest Edits
Chainlink VRF allows you to integrate provably-fair and verifiably random data in your smart contract.

For implementation details, read Introduction to Chainlink VRF.

Polygon (Matic) Mainnet
Important

The LINK provided by the Polygon (Matic) Bridge is not ERC-677 compatible, so cannot be 
used with Chainlink oracles. However, it can be converted to the official LINK token on Polygon (Matic) using
Chainlink's PegSwap service

Item	Value
LINK Token	0xb0897686c545045aFc77CF20eC7A532E3120E0F1
VRF Coordinator	0x3d2341ADb2D31f1c5530cDC622016af293177AE0
Key Hash	0xf86195cf7690c55907b2b611ebb7343a6f649bff128701cc542f0569e2c549da
Fee	0.0001 LINK
VRF Response Times on Polygon

VRF responses are generated after 10 block confirmations on Polygon by default. 
Please get in touch with us if you require VRF responses to be
generated after a higher number of block confirmations, based on what 
you feel is best for achieving secure finality times on Polygon.


Source - https://docs.chain.link/docs/vrf-contracts/
